<figureCitation box="[757,862,884,910]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[136,229,1994,2016]" captionStartId-1="3.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox-0="[202,1385,248,1954]" captionTargetBox-1="[247,1352,212,1994]" captionTargetId-0="figure-47@2.[193,1395,242,1966]" captionTargetId-1="figure-30@3.[223,1364,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1 Nymphanthus calcicola S.R. Yi &amp; Gang Yao.A‒C. Male plant; D‒F. Female plant; G‒H. Male flower; I‒J. Female flower; K. Fruits; L. Disk glands and pistil of female flower; M. Disk glands and stamens of male flower; N. Ovaries and styles; O. Seeds. (based on the type materal, photoed S. R. Yi)" captionText-1="FIGURE 2 Holotype (E.M. Bodinier 2194; E-00327392) of Nymphanthus bodinieri (Levl.) R.W. Bouman. Female flowers inserted at upper part of branchlets, male flowers inserted at lower part of branchlets." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6673281" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6673283" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6673281/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6673283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Figs. 1‒2</figureCitation>
